The files found in this settings directory include the following:
  Custom packages that can be loaded into any notebook.
  Custom settings that set things like the "Show Input" toggle button or having a ruler toolbar
     enabled by default

Everything in this settings directory should be moved to $UserBaseDirectory/__ as specified below.

Note: $UserBaseDirectory is the base user's directory specified by Mathematica.  You can get this value 
from any Mathematica notebook by typing '$UserBaseDirectory' into the notebook.

Customizations should be placed in $UserBaseDirectory/Autoload/

All packages (any directory found in ./packages/) should be placed in $UserBaseDirectory/Applications/
For instance: 
  Braindrop should be placed in $UserBaseDirectory/Applications/
  Neurogrid should be placed in $UserBaseDirectory/Applications/
